{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"fields":{"description":"## Why\nWith many attestations every consumer must address a specific kind, without breaking the existing single-verdict API/CLI/MCP/schema.\n## What\n`verify_signature(ticket_id, kind=\"plan-review\")` ALWAYS returns a SINGLE verdict dict\n(schema `verify_signature_result.schema.json` UNCHANGED); `kind` defaults to `\"plan-review\"`\nso existing no-kind callers keep back-compat. Internally it reads\n`state[\"attestations\"][kind]`, falling back to the legacy `state[\"signature\"]` mirror when\nthe map is absent. Add a SEPARATE `verify_attestations(ticket_id) -> {kind: verdict}`\nentry-point for the verify-all map (NOT a new return shape of `verify_signature`). CLI:\n`--kind K` = single-gate exit code; no `--kind` = human-readable listing via\n`verify_attestations` (exit 0 iff all certified). MCP `verify_signature` stays single\n(kind defaults to plan-review). SCOPE BOUNDARY: this story owns the `verify_signature` MCP\ntool + its (unchanged) result schema; the `attestations` field in the ticket-state MCP\nresponse is owned by ed26.\n## Scope\n`src/rebar/signing.py` (`verify_signature` add `kind=`, `verify_attestations`,\n`verify_signature_cli`), `src/rebar/mcp_server.py` (verify tool only).\n## Depends on\nRequires 114f merged (reads `state[\"attestations\"]`).\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] `verify_signature(ticket_id, kind=\"plan-review\")` returns a single verdict; reads `attestations[kind]` with legacy `signature` fallback; schema unchanged.\n- [ ] `verify_attestations(ticket_id)` returns `{kind: verdict}` over all present attestations.\n- [ ] CLI `--kind K` exit 0 iff that kind certified; no `--kind` lists all, exit 0 iff all certified.\n- [ ] Existing no-kind library/MCP callers keep single-verdict back-compat (default kind plan-review).\n- [ ] Legacy single-signature ticket verifies under its derived kind."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1782794435242618001,"uuid":"11f63248-1c22-4783-b7be-2b044e191bfe"}